  "local_port": 60870,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much does it cost to build a robot?",
  "response": "The cost to build a robot can vary widely depending on various factors such as the type, size, complexity, materials used, and the intended purpose of the robot. Here are some rough estimates for different types of robots:\n\n1. ** Hobbyist or DIY Robots:**\n   - **Simple Robots (e.g., line-following robots, basic remote-controlled robots):** \n     - Cost can range from $50 to $300. These typically use inexpensive components like Arduino or Raspberry Pi, motors, sensors, and basic materials.\n   - **More Advanced Hobbyist Robots (e.g., humanoid robots, autonomous robots):** \n     - Costs can range from $300 to $2,000 or more, depending on the components and sophistication.\n\n2. **Educational Robots:**\n   - **Robots used in educational settings, like LEGO Mindstorms or VEX Robotics kits:**\n     - These can range from $300 to $1,000, depending on the kit and additional components.\n\n3. **Industrial Robots:**\n   - **Robotic Arms and Manipulators:**\n     - Costs can range from $10,000 to $100,000 or more, depending on payload capacity, reach, precision, and brand.\n   - **Automated Guided Vehicles (AGVs):**\n     - These can cost anywhere from $20,000 to over $100,000.\n\n4. **Service Robots:**\n   - **Robots used in healthcare, hospitality, or cleaning:**\n     - These can range from $10,000 to $50,000 or more, depending on their capabilities and customization.\n\n5. **Research and Development Robots:**\n   - **Highly specialized robots for research purposes:**\n     - Costs can range from $50,000 to several million dollars, depending on the complexity and the technology involved.\n\n6. **Consumer Robots:**\n   - **Robotic vacuum cleaners, lawn mowers, etc.:**\n     - These can range from $200 to $2,000.\n\nTo get a more precise estimate, you'd need to consider the specific requirements of your robot project, including:\n- The type and quality of components (sensors, motors, microcontrollers, etc.)\n- Customization and design work\n- Labor costs if you're hiring professionals\n- Testing and iteration costs\n\nIf you provide more details about the specific robot you're interested in building, I can give you a more tailored estimate.",
